          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p>The key insight: if your probiotic contains a mix of Lactobacillus and Bifidobacterium strains (which most multi-strain products do), default to taking it on an empty stomach before a meal. This protocol protects the most acid-sensitive strains in the blend. If your product is exclusively spore-based (Bacillus), take it with food — the spores actually germinate more effectively in the presence of nutrients. For comprehensive digestive support beyond probiotics, our guide to <a href="/vitamins/digestion-gummies/">digestion gummies</a> covers enzyme blends, ginger, and other gut-health formulations.</p>

    <div class="tip-box" style="background:#F1F8E9;border-color:#AED581;">
      <div class="tip-box-ico" style="background:#4CAF50;">★</div>
      <div>
        <p><strong>Our #1 Pick: Goli Probiotic+</strong></p>
        <p style="margin-top:4px;">World's first 3-in-1 pre+pro+postbiotic gummy. Shelf-stable, no refrigeration. <a href="/vitamins/probiotic-gummies/" style="color:#2E7D32;font-weight:600;">See full review & buy →</a></p>
